---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Ghostworks is an independent research effort building self-evolving AI agent systems."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <Hero
    eyebrow="About"
    title="Building from theory to deployment."
    subtitle="Ghostworks is an independent research effort focused on bridging the translation gap between cognitive science theory and operational AI agent systems."
  />

  <section class="container-content pb-16 animate-fade-up">
    <div class="surface-glow rounded-lg border border-border bg-bg-subtle p-8 sm:p-10">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-wider text-fg-subtle">The Mission</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Make cognitive architectures operational.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-fg-muted">
          <p>
            Theories like Global Workspace Theory, Integrated Information Theory, and predictive
            processing have shaped how we think about cognition for decades. But they almost always
            stop at descriptions. Running them as actual control systems for autonomous agents, with
            measurable behavior, calibrated parameters, and stability guarantees, is rarely
            attempted in the open.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ghostworks treats that translation gap as the work itself. Every framework here is
            published with full pseudocode, parameter values, stability tests, and real cycle data.
            Reproducible enough to be audited, structured enough to be built upon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-content pb-16 animate-fade-up stagger-1">
    <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-wider text-fg-subtle">What's Public</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Open research, incremental release.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-fg-muted">
        <p>
          The research repository mirrors an actively evolving private deployment. Specifications,
          pseudocode, parameter values, stability tests, and cycle logs are published openly.
          Executable pipeline scripts are released as they stabilize.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is a research and specification publication first, not a polished install-and-run
          package. The goal is to make the system auditable and reproducible, not to ship a product.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-content pb-16 animate-fade-up stagger-1">
    <div class="surface-glow rounded-lg border border-border bg-bg-subtle p-8 sm:p-10">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-wider text-fg-subtle">Team</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Independent research, operational depth.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-fg-muted">
          <p>
            Ghostworks is an independent research effort. The founding team brings together
            expertise across cognitive systems architecture, machine learning engineering, and
            formal verification — the combination required to build architectures that are both
            theoretically grounded and operationally stable.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our work spans the full stack: from drive calculus and boredom mechanics at the
            cognitive layer, through execution trace capture and gradient computation at the
            research layer, down to stability test batteries, memory integrity verification, and
            deployment orchestration.
          </p>
          <p>
            We publish openly because the field advances faster when architectures are reproducible
            and auditable. Every framework on this site includes the same specification depth we
            use internally — parameter values, stability results, and cycle data.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-content pb-24 animate-fade-up stagger-2">
    <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-wider text-fg-subtle">What's Next</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">The path forward.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-fg-muted">
        <p>
          GNW is moving through Phase 6: cross-agent coordination, drive score broadcast, weight
          sharing, multi-agent synchronization. GRAO is entering its exploration phase after
          detecting policy saturation at round 39.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beyond that: self-modifying drives that calibrate from success/failure rates, cross-session
          memory integration, and a full multi-agent orchestration layer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>




